1. Install PostgreSQL 17
sudo dnf install -y https://download.postgresql.org/pub/repos/yum/reporpms/EL-9-x86_64/pgdg-redhat-repo-latest.noarch.rpm
sudo dnf -qy module disable postgresql
sudo dnf install -y postgresql17-server

##Do not run postgresql-17-setup initdb â€” Patroni will handle initialization.

2. Install Patroni
sudo dnf install -y patroni patroni-etcd

3. Configure Patroni
Use the configuration files provided in this repository as the base.

4.start and enable patroni
sudo systemctl enable patroni
sudo systemctl start patroni

##Patroni will:
Bootstrap the first node as leader
Initialize PostgreSQL data directory
Register other nodes as replicas automatically

5.Check cluster status:
patronictl -c /etc/patroni.yml list

6.Test Failover
sudo systemctl stop patroni   # on leader
patronictl -c /etc/patroni.yml list
